### Task: Fix Shopify webhook signature validation

ASSUMPTIONS:
- The HMAC comparison uses the shop's API secret, not the app secret (Shopify docs confirm this)
- Webhook body must be read as raw bytes before JSON parsing (hashing parsed JSON changes the hash)
- The X-Shopify-Hmac-SHA256 header contains base64-encoded HMAC-SHA256

UNKNOWNS:
- Whether the current FastAPI middleware consumes the request body before our handler reads it
- Whether proxy headers (X-Forwarded-For) affect the signature

VERIFICATION_PLAN:
- Capture a real webhook payload from Shopify (use ngrok + print raw body)
- Compute HMAC locally and compare against header value
- Test with both valid and tampered payloads

STATUS: in_progress

